                        <condition key="other">
                           <p>Good. The threads of the sewing seem to be of animal origin. The gutter of the quires are slightly affected with humidity. Some leaves are damaged by rodents, fol. <locus target="#1"/>-<locus target="#2"/>
                              <locus from="20" to="37"/>, <locus from="73" to="77"/>, <locus target="#99"/>by worms. </p>
                           <p>Some of the folios show traces of trimming (see fol. <locus target="#17r #52v #82r #99v"/>). Stabs remainening from six leaves are visible between the last text quire and the back board. An iron nail is driven in the left bottom corner of the back board. </p>
                           <p>A note on paper slip, written in English in European hand, concerning the Ethiopic language and Ethiopic Bible, and Royal Library ex libris are pasted on the inner side of the front board. Another English note concerning the content of the manuscript, written on yellow paper, is attached to fol. <locus target="#1a"/>. </p>
                           
                        </condition>
